There are three components required to run a single node cluster (minikube)
1. Virtual Box
2. minikube.exe
3. kubectl

Commands That I ran to deploy minikube single node cluster
1. minikube delete -> To delete any minikube particles
2. minikube start -> To deploy a Virtual Box minikube VM and a Kubernetes cluster
3. kubectl get pods --all-namespaces
4. kubectl get nodes -o wide
5. kubectl cluster-info
6. kubectl cluster-info dump
7. kubectl run hello-minikube --image=k8s.gcr.io/echoserver:1.4 --port=8080
8. kubectl get pods
9. kubectl expose deployment hello-minikube --type=NodePort
10. minikube service hello-minikube --url
11. kubectl delete deployment hello-minikube
12. minikube stop
13. minikube delete

